# Color Palette

The app must use **black, white, and shades of gray only** until further notice.

**Exception:** Badges, tags, and labels may use color (e.g. status badges like draft/published, status pills, category tags).

## When adding or modifying UI

- Use `black`, `white`, and Tailwind gray scale (`gray-50` through `gray-950`)
- No blue, green, red, yellow, etc. for buttons, links, backgrounds, borders, or text (except in badges/tags/labels)
- Links: use gray text with hover underline or similar, not colored text
- Buttons: use gray scale (e.g. `bg-gray-900`, `bg-gray-100`), not colored backgrounds
- Borders: gray only

## Allowed color usage

- Badges (e.g. post status: draft, published, scheduled, archived)
- Tags and labels
- Category pills or similar

## Examples

```
// ❌ Colored buttons
className="bg-blue-600 text-white"

// ✅ Gray scale
className="bg-gray-900 text-white"
className="bg-gray-200 text-gray-900"
```
